-- Dados da tabela questions
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (1, 'You are managing a new software development project that is critical to the company''s future. External stakeholders have the power to influence the project significantly.  What should you do during the project planning stage to ensure that you can manage the external stakeholder''s influence effectively?', '["Identify the external stakeholders during the initiation", "Use a stakeholder engagement assessment matrix", "Create a RACI matrix for the project", "Develop a stakeholder management plan"]', 3, 'A stakeholder management plan is a component of the project management plan that is created during the project planning stage. A project stakeholder management plan specifies the management strategies that will be used to effectively engage stakeholders during the project. The strategies include the levels of stakeholder engagement, the frequency of their involvement, and the escalation path in case of any issues. The stakeholder management plan will help the project manager identify the external stakeholders who may have the power or interest to stop the project, and plan how to manage their influence effectively. A stakeholder engagement assessment matrix is a tool that can be used to develop the stakeholder management plan. The matrix is a grid that maps stakeholders based on their level of authority and their level of interest in the project. Using the stakeholder engagement assessment matrix, the project team can determine the level of interest and influence of the stakeholders on the project and develop a plan to keep stakeholders satisfied.', 'Gestão de Stakeholders', '2025-05-16 23:46:34', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', NULL, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (2, 'As the project manager, you are in the process of developing the project charter for a large project. You need to specify the key project stakeholders in the project charter.  What should you do first?', '["Document the common project risks in the risk register", "Consult the enterprise environmental factors and organizational process assets", "Review the lessons learned register from previous projects", "Identify potential key stakeholders"]', 3, 'The question states that as the project manager, you need to specify the key project stakeholders in the project charter. You will need to conduct the Identify Stakeholders process to identify potential key stakeholders. The Identify Stakeholders process is the process of identifying all people or organizations impacted by the project, and documenting relevant information regarding their interests, involvement, interdependencies, influence, and potential impact on project success. Conducting the Identify Stakeholders process is the first step in the Stakeholder Management Knowledge Area and is the only process that is part of the Project Integration Management Knowledge Area. Once the key stakeholders are identified, the project manager can specify them in the project charter.', 'Gestão de Stakeholders', '2025-05-16 23:46:34', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', NULL, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (3, 'You are a project manager who is in the process of defining the project. You have identified several stakeholders and are now planning the stakeholder management. You want to analyze the stakeholders'' needs, potential impacts, and levels of authority.  What should you do first?', '["Identify the stakeholders and their levels of authority", "Identify the stakeholders'' needs and potential impacts", "Conduct an environmental assessment of the organization", "Create a stakeholder management plan for the project"]', 1, 'The scenario describes the process of stakeholder analysis and the development of a stakeholder register, which occurs during the Identify Stakeholders process. The question is asking what should be done first during this process. In order to identify the stakeholders, the project manager may use an environmental assessment. The environmental assessment is a mechanism for capturing, reviewing, and assessing relevant information concerning the stakeholders and their interests, the organization''s political and social structure, the marketplace, the industry, and the project itself that can influence the project. The environmental assessment is a good starting point for identifying the stakeholders'' needs and potential impacts', 'Gestão de Stakeholders', '2025-05-16 23:46:34', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', NULL, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (4, 'A project manager is using a RAM (Responsibility Assignment Matrix) to define the responsibilities of the project team members. The project manager is trying to determine what level of detail to include in the RAM.  What should the project manager do to help determine the level of detail to include in the RAM?', '["Construct a stakeholder engagement assessment matrix", "Create a RACI chart", "Establish a resource breakdown structure (RBS)", "Prepare a stakeholder register"]', 3, 'The scenario implies that the project manager is working on the Identify Stakeholders process. A responsibility assignment matrix (RAM) is a grid that shows the project resources assigned to each work package. The RAM is used to illustrate the connections between work packages or activities and project team members. The project manager is trying to determine what level of detail to include in the RAM. The level of detail would be determined by the number and types of resources and activities. Before the project manager can create a RAM, the project manager must first make a list of the project resources. This list of project resources is the stakeholder register, which is an output of the Identify Stakeholders process. The stakeholder register includes the roles and responsibilities of each stakeholder. Once the project manager has the stakeholder register, the project manager can then create a RAM. Without the stakeholder register, the project manager would not know what resources should be included in the RAM. Therefore, to help determine what level of detail to include in the RAM, the project manager should first prepare the stakeholder register', 'Gestão de Stakeholders', '2025-05-16 23:46:34', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', NULL, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (5, 'You are a project manager for a software development project. You have just completed the verification of the project''s deliverables and have determined that all the acceptance criteria have been met.  What should you do next?', '["Updating the lessons learned register and organizational process assets", "Performing the Close Project or Phase process", "Generating work performance data and work performance information", "Compiling the final project report, which includes the lessons learned"]', 1, 'Based on the scenario, you have just completed the Verify Deliverables process. The Verify Deliverables process is the process of formalizing acceptance of completed project deliverables. The key benefit of this process is that it provides an accepted deliverable that can be used to gain formal acceptance of the project''s product. The Verify Deliverables process generally takes place after the Control Quality process has validated the deliverables and is typically managed and supervised by the project manager. The project manager, project team, and relevant stakeholders should have previously agreed on the acceptance criteria, which are used to assess whether the deliverables are acceptable and satisfactory. Once the deliverables have been verified, accepted, and approved, they become an input to the Control Procurements process and to the Close Project or Phase process. The Close Project or Phase process is the process of finalizing all activities for the project, phase, or contract. The key benefit of this process is that it provides a transition of the project or phase''s product, service, or result as well as historical information to the responsible organization. The Close Project or Phase process should be performed after each phase and at the end of the project. It is described in the Project Integration Management knowledge area in the Monitor and Control Project Work process, and the Direct and Manage Project Work process, and is also referenced in the Project Scope Management knowledge area in the Collect Requirements, Define Scope, and Validate Scope processes.', 'Gestão do Escopo', '2025-05-16 23:59:32', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', NULL, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (6, 'When the project manager and project team decide to implement a change request, which of the following is the first thing they should do?', '["Develop an approved change request to implement the change", "Update the project management plan and project documents", "Revise the requirements documentation and update the requirements traceability matrix", "Create a work performance report to communicate the impact of the change"]', 1, 'Per the PMBOK Guide, the Develop Project Management Plan process is the process of defining, preparing, and coordinating all plan components and consolidating them into the project management plan. Initial project documents that may be developed as outputs from the Develop Project Management Plan process might include a change management plan, a requirements management plan, and a configuration management plan. The project management plan, including these subsidiary plans and baselines, is used as an input to the Develop Project Team process. The scenario suggests that a decision has been made to implement a change request. The initial project documents, including the change management plan, may need to be updated to reflect that decision and ensure that the change request is implemented in a controlled manner. The scenario does not suggest that a change request was submitted and that the project management plan and project documents are to be updated to reflect the approved changes. Therefore, of the available choices, updating the project management plan and project documents is the best answer to the question asked', 'Gestão do Escopo', '2025-05-16 23:59:32', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', NULL, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (7, 'You are a project manager for a software development project that uses an iterative product development approach. The project team has just completed the third iteration of the product.  What should you do next?', '["Update the iteration backlog with the remaining work", "Review the iteration deliverables with the project team", "Meet with the project team to create a new iteration plan", "Obtain stakeholder feedback and prepare for the next iteration"]', 3, 'You are a project manager for a software development project that uses an iterative product development approach. The project team has just completed the third iteration of the product. The question implies that you have completed the Monitor and Control Project Work process. The output of this process is work performance information. The question is asking what you should do next. Based on the available choices, the best answer is to use the work performance information to obtain feedback from the stakeholders. The stakeholder feedback will help you make decisions about what to include in the next iteration. In an adaptive environment, the process of defining the requirements for the next iteration can be very short, but it is essential to gather the stakeholder feedback before proceeding with the next iteration. The other answer choices might be performed at some point in the project, but they are not the next steps in the scenario described in the question.', 'Gestão do Escopo', '2025-05-16 23:59:32', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', NULL, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (8, 'You are managing a new project that will deliver a system upgrade for a customer. You are working with the customer''s project manager to develop the project charter. The customer''s project manager is not familiar with the creation process of the project charter.  What is the first thing you should do in this situation?', '["Request the project charter from the project sponsor", "Advise the customer''s project manager to create the project charter", "Ask the project sponsor to provide an overview of the project charter", "Recommend that the customer''s project manager review the project charter template"]', 3, 'The scenario implies that the customer''s project manager is not familiar with the creation process of the project charter. The development of a project charter is a team effort that involves the project sponsor, the project manager, and other key stakeholders. The first thing the customer''s project manager should do is review the project charter template. The template can be used as a guideline for the information that is typically included in the project charter. The project charter template may vary from organization to organization and from project to project. The project charter is considered a best practice that may or may not be used by an organization. If a project charter is not used, the information contained in a project charter should be included in some other document and made available to stakeholders. The project charter is typically developed by the project sponsor. The project manager should obtain the project charter from the project sponsor and share it with the customer''s project manager. The project sponsor should also be available to answer any questions the customer''s project manager may have regarding the project charter.', 'Gestão do Escopo', '2025-05-16 23:59:32', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', NULL, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (9, 'You are in the process of identifying and categorizing your stakeholders for your project. You have identified an individual who is very interested in the project but has very little power to influence it.  What is the best way to categorize this individual?', '["Low power, high interest", "High power, high interest", "Low power, low interest", "High power, low interest"]', 3, 'The stakeholder described in the scenario is a latent stakeholder. Latent stakeholders have low power to influence the project and have low interest in it. The other stakeholders in the matrix you are completing probably have more power and interest in the project. The matrix you are completing is probably the Power/Interest Grid. The Power/Interest Grid is a useful way to categorize and display stakeholders'' power and interest. The four quadrants of the Power/Interest Grid are as follows: High power, high interest (Key Players), High power, low interest (Keep Satisfied), Low power, high interest (Keep Informed), Low power, low interest (Monitor). The stakeholder in the scenario has been classified as having low power and low interest which makes him a Monitor.', 'Gestão do Tempo', '2025-05-17 00:04:24', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', 11, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (10, 'You are leading a project to build a new bridge. The project is in the planning phase, and you are currently developing the project management plan. You need to define the activities and dependencies.  What is the most detailed tool that you could use to accomplish this task?', '["Decomposition", "Expert judgment", "Rolling wave planning", "Arrow diagramming method"]', 3, 'The question requires you to identify the tool and technique that is the most detailed of the available choices. The available choices, in order of decreasing detail, are: 1. Decomposition 2. Rolling wave planning 3. Expert judgment 4. Arrow diagramming method  5. Analogous estimating  The arrow diagramming method (ADM) is a schedule network diagramming technique that uses boxes or nodes to represent activities and arrows to represent the relationships between activities. The length of the arrow represents the duration of the activity. ADM is the most detailed of the available choices and is, therefore, the best answer to the question asked.  Of the remaining choices, analogous estimating, and expert judgment are both tools used during the Develop Schedule process. Decomposition is a tool used during the Define Activities process, and rolling wave planning is used during the Develop Schedule process.', 'Gestão do Tempo', '2025-05-17 00:04:24', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', 11, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (11, 'You are leading a team to develop a new software application. The project is using an agile approach with two-week iterations. The product owner is working with the team to create and prioritize user stories for the first release.  Which agile ceremony should be conducted first in the upcoming iteration?', '["Sprint review", "Daily stand-up", "Sprint retrospective", "Sprint planning"]', 3, 'The software application development project described is using an agile approach of Scrum. The project is in the first iteration and the product owner is working with the team to create and prioritize user stories for the first release. The question asks which ceremony should be conducted first in the upcoming iteration. The possible ceremonies for a Scrum project are the sprint review and the sprint planning. Since the team has not yet executed the iteration, the ceremonies from the previous iteration would be the sprint review and retrospective. Therefore, the upcoming ceremony is the sprint planning. In the sprint planning, the team selects the user stories from the product backlog to be included in the upcoming iteration and decomposes those user stories into tasks. The team then uses the decomposed tasks to create the sprint backlog. The team cannot conduct the sprint review until the end of the iteration and the team cannot conduct the sprint retrospective until after the sprint review. Therefore, the sprint planning ceremony should be conducted first in the upcoming iteration.', 'Gestão do Tempo', '2025-05-17 00:04:24', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', 11, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (12, 'During the execution of the project, you realize the cost performance index is 0.7.  What should you do first?', '["Determine if the project is under or over budget", "Determine if the project is under or over the scope", "Determine if the project is under or over the schedule", "Update the project management plan and project documents"]', 0, 'The cost performance index (CPI) is the ratio of the actual work performed to the actual costs incurred. The CPI provides a measure of cost efficiency on a project. A value of less than 1.0 indicates that the project is over budget. In the scenario described, the CPI of 0.7 indicates that the project is over budget. Therefore, the first thing you should do is determine if the project is under or over budget.', 'Gestão do Tempo', '2025-05-17 00:04:24', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', 11, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (13, 'You are managing a project to develop a new software application. The project is currently in the execution phase.  What should you do next?', '["Develop project communications", "Manage stakeholder engagement", "Distribute information to project stakeholders", "Update the project management plan"]', 0, 'The scenario implies that you are completing project communications management activities. You are executing the project and according to the PMBOK Guide, the Develop Project Communications process is part of the Executing Process Group. This process is primarily concerned with creating the project communications that were planned in the Plan Communications Management process. An output of the Develop Project Communications process is project presentations, which may include project status presentations. As the scenario describes a situation where the project is currently in the execution phase, it is likely that you are performing many of the Executing Process Group processes including the Develop Project Communications process. Therefore, of the available options, develop project communications is what you should do next', 'Gestão das Comunicações', '2025-05-17 00:06:38', '1-principais competências de um Gerente de projetos.pdf', 4, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (14, 'You are a project manager for a project that has been divided into many component projects. You want to ensure that the component projects are managed in a coordinated way.  What should you do?', '["Contact the program manager for advice on managing programs", "Request a change to the project management plan", "Develop a project communications management plan", "Hold a meeting with the project stakeholders to discuss the coordination of the component projects"]', 2, 'The project described in the scenario is an example of a program. A program is a group of related projects managed in a coordinated way. The project manager is managing one of the component projects. Programs will have a program manager who is responsible for managing the entire program. The program manager will be responsible for developing a program communications management plan to manage communications across the program, including the component projects. The program communications management plan is a component of the program management plan, and it can be thought of as a super set of the project communications management plan.', 'Gestão das Comunicações', '2025-05-17 00:06:38', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', 11, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (15, 'A project has just started, and the project manager is planning the risk management. The project manager has asked the other team members to provide input on how to conduct risk management for their particular areas of responsibility.  What is the most likely reason the project manager is seeking this input?', '["The project manager is seeking input to identify the project''s risk owners", "The project manager is seeking input to determine the project''s risk appetite", "The project manager is seeking input to assess the project''s risk exposure", "The project manager is seeking input to identify the stakeholders'' risk tolerances"]', 3, 'The scenario describes a project that has just started, and the project manager is planning the risk management. This implies that the Identify Risks process is being performed as part of the initial risk management planning. The project manager is asking the other team members to provide input on how to conduct risk management for their particular areas of responsibility. This implies that the other team members are responsible for the work performance data and work performance reports that are the outputs of the Direct and Manage Project Work process. Both of these outputs are used as inputs for the Identify Risks process. The work performance data provides the actual data collected from the project, and work performance reports provide the information on the project''s performance that is included in the status reports. The team members have access to the actual data collected and the project''s status that will help the project manager and the team identify possible sources of risk events. Therefore, the most likely reason the project manager is seeking this input is to identify the stakeholders'' risk tolerances', 'Gestão das Comunicações', '2025-05-17 00:06:38', '1-principais competências de um Gerente de projetos.pdf', 3, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (16, 'A project for building a bridge is being planned. The project team has identified several risks related to the reliability of the construction equipment. The project manager has requested assistance with the selection of the best risk response strategies for the identified risks.  What is the most suitable response for the project manager?', '["Risk acceptance", "Expert judgment", "Risk mitigation", "Risk avoidance"]', 3, 'The scenario describes a situation in which the project manager is in the process of planning risk responses. One technique that can be used during this process is expert judgment. The project manager is seeking the advice of a subject-matter expert on the risk response strategies that are most appropriate for the identified risks. Of the available answer choices, only risk avoidance represents a risk response strategy. Risk avoidance is a technique for dealing with a threat by removing its cause. For example, when building a bridge, the engineers may decide to avoid the risk of the construction equipment failing by leasing new equipment instead of using older, less reliable equipment. The other answer choices are not risk response strategies. Note that while the project manager may be seeking the expert''s opinion on the risk response strategies, the project manager is the one responsible for selecting the strategies', 'Gestão das Comunicações', '2025-05-17 00:06:38', '1-principais competências de um Gerente de projetos.pdf', 1, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (17, 'You are a project manager who is about to start planning a high-profile project. As a first step, you want to determine the project stakeholders, their information needs, and how that information will be communicated.  What is the first thing that you should do?', '["Establish the project management plan", "Develop the Project Management Plan", "Identify the project stakeholders", "Identify the project risks"]', 1, 'The scenario describes the process of identifying stakeholders. This process is part of the project communications management knowledge area and is the first step in the project communications planning process. The project management plan is an output of the Develop Project Management Plan process. The project management plan describes how the project will be executed, monitored and controlled, and closed. It is used to communicate how the project will be managed, executed, and controlled. The project management plan is the primary output of the Develop Project Management Plan process and is an input to the Identify Stakeholders process and its sub-process, the Plan Communications Management process. The project management plan is an essential document used to develop the stakeholder register, a project document that is part of the project communications planning process.', 'Gestão das Comunicações', '2025-05-17 00:06:38', '1-principais competências de um Gerente de projetos.pdf', 4, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (18, 'The project is underway, and you have just learned that the team is not using the risk register that you spent so much time developing.  How do you motivate the team to use the risk register?', '["Include a tool requirement in the project management plan to enforce the team''s use of the risk register", "Work with the team to understand why they are not using the risk register and then adjust your approach accordingly", "Escalate the issue to the project sponsor to determine how the team can be forced to use the risk register", "Incorporate the risk register into the project''s quality management process to ensure that the team uses the register"]', 1, 'The question implies that the project manager has ''taken'' a methodical approach to risk management by developing a risk register with the project team. It is a good practice for the project manager to work with the project team to identify project risks, analyze the risks, and develop a risk register that includes all identified risks, their potential impact on the project''s objectives, and the planned responses to the risks. However, this approach may not always be the best approach for a given project. Risk management is about balancing the need for proactive risk management with the realities of the project and the organization. The project manager should not blindly follow a set of ''best practices'' if they are not helping the project or the organization achieve their objectives. The project manager should use their soft skills to work with the project team and the stakeholders to understand the underlying reasons why the risk register is not being used and adjust the risk management process accordingly.', 'Gestão dos Riscos', '2025-05-17 00:11:12', '9-Planning_ Risk Management.pdf', 17, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (19, 'You are the project manager of the company''s new product development project. You have established a change control board (CCB) and developed a process for managing change requests. You are now in the process of managing the approved change requests.  What is the first thing you should do when a change request is approved by the CCB?', '["Inform the stakeholders of the approved change request", "Submit a request for change to the CCB", "Analyze the impact of the change request", "Update the issue log with the approved change request"]', 2, 'When a change request is approved, you should perform an analysis of the impact of the change on the project as a whole. This analysis is called the impact analysis. This analysis will help to determine whether the change request should be implemented as requested, modified, or denied. The impact analysis may also identify any new risks that may be created by the change request. The risk management plan should document how the impact analysis will be conducted. Therefore, of the available choices, analyzing the impact of the change request is the first thing you should do when a change request is approved by the CCB', 'Gestão dos Riscos', '2025-05-17 00:11:12', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', 9, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (20, 'You are managing a project to develop a new product for your company. The overall project schedule and budget are fixed, but you have some flexibility in the requirements and technical features of the product.  Which of the following is critical to understand for this project?', '["The sources of project risk", "The quality of the project management plan", "The team''s understanding of the project scope definition", "The level of tolerance for the project risk exposure"]', 0, 'The project is in the planning stage and project risk management is an essential part of the project management plan that is developed during the Planning Process Group. The project risk management plan is one of the components of the project management plan and describes how risk management will be structured and performed on the project. The project risk management plan is not a fixed scope, schedule, or cost and, therefore, is one of the flexible aspects of the project. The risk management plan is required by the PMBOK® Guide and explicitly mentioned in the description of the project scenario', 'Gestão dos Riscos', '2025-05-17 00:11:12', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', 9, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (21, 'You are leading the development of a new product for your company. You have determined that the project is at risk of not meeting its schedule commitments due to the possibility of changes in the availability of the resources required to perform the work.  What is the best way to address this risk?', '["Resource smoothing", "Resource allocation", "Resource loading", "Resource leveling"]', 3, 'The scenario states that the project is at risk of not meeting its schedule commitments due to the possibility of changes in the availability of the resources required to perform the work. The question is asking for the best way to address this risk. Adding or adjusting the project team, physical resources, or the amount of time and money available for the project may be necessary to address the risk of not meeting the schedule commitments. Resource leveling is a technique in which start and finish dates are adjusted based on resource constraints with the goal of balancing demand for resources with the available supply. Resource leveling is a form of what-if scenario analysis and can be used in conjunction with other risk response strategies.', 'Gestão dos Riscos', '2025-05-17 00:11:12', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', 9, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (22, 'You are managing a project to develop a new product. You have just completed the qualitative risk analysis process.  What should you do next?', '["Analyze the probability and potential impact of the identified risks", "Update the project documents", "Update the risk register with the results of the qualitative risk analysis", "Develop risk responses to the identified risks that have been prioritized"]', 1, 'The question states that the project manager has just completed the qualitative risk analysis process. The process that is performed next after qualitative risk analysis in the Plan Risk Management process is the update of the project documents. The project documents that may be updated as part of the Plan Risk Management process include the risk register. The risk register is a key project document that lists and classifies the project''s risks and provides information on the qualitative and quantitative risk analysis. The risk register is used to track the status of the project''s risks and the results of the risk management processes. In this scenario, the risk register may be updated to reflect the results of the qualitative risk analysis. For example, the assessment of the probability and impact of the risks may be updated, as well as the list of the key assumptions made during the risk identification process. The risk register may also be updated with the list of risks that have a high probability and impact and will be analyzed further as part of the quantitative risk analysis process', 'Gestão dos Riscos', '2025-05-17 00:11:12', '9-Planning_ Risk Management.pdf', 17, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (23, 'You are managing a project to build a new bridge. You realize that a key material, concrete, is not available with the quality and volume you need.  What is the best solution to address this issue?', '["Use or lose contract", "Cost plus incentive fee contract", "Cost plus fixed fee contract", "Cost plus award fee contract"]', 0, 'You are the project manager of a bridge construction project and you realize that there is a shortage of concrete supplies. As a result, you must find a solution to address the shortage of concrete. You have been managing the project to build a new bridge and have realized that a key material, concrete, is not available in the quantity and quality you need. Of the available choices, the use or lose contract would be the best solution to address this issue. The use or lose contract will motivate the seller to obtain the required concrete supplies before the end of the contract or risk losing the money for the unused concrete. This type of contract would be most appropriate in a situation where time is of the essence. The project is already underway, and the concrete supplies are needed immediately to avoid delaying the project and the associated costs of the delay. The use or lose contract is an example of a fixed-price incentive fee contract. In this type of contract, the seller receives a financial incentive for meeting or exceeding selected project objectives, such as schedule targets. The use or lose provision is one example of a project objective that can be used to motivate the seller to perform in a certain manner. The other contract types presented in the answer choices are not as effective at motivating the seller to perform in a specific way as the use or lose contract. Therefore, of the available choices, the use or lose contract is the best solution to address the scenario described', 'Gestão das Aquisições', '2025-05-17 00:13:49', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', 12, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (24, 'You are a project manager for a software development project. The project is being executed in a highly regulated environment with stringent change control requirements. The project management plan and other project documents are kept under strict configuration control.  The project is currently in the planning phase and you are working with the project team to decompose the work packages into scheduling activities.  To which process should you refer to understand the methodology for developing the project schedule?', '["Desenvolver o Cronograma", "Sequenciar as Atividades", "Planilhar Recursos das Atividades", "Definir as Atividades"]', 0, 'The scenario describes a project manager who is in the process of defining a method for sequencing activities as part of the development of the project schedule. Developing the project schedule is the process of analyzing activity sequences, durations, resource requirements, and schedule constraints to create the project schedule. The methodology for sequencing activities is an output of the Define Activities process and an input to the Develop Schedule process. The schedule methodology is an approach to sequencing activities that is used to develop the project schedule. The methodology can be simple or detailed. The scenario implies that the project manager is defining a detailed schedule methodology. Therefore, of the available choices, the Develop Schedule process is the best answer to the question posed.', 'Gestão das Aquisições', '2025-05-17 00:13:49', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', 12, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (25, 'During the execution of a project, a key stakeholder requests an increase in the scope of the project. The project manager is not able to convince the stakeholder of the negative consequences of the request, and the change is approved.  What is the project manager''s best course of action?', '["Update the project management plan and any other project documents", "Make the requested changes in the project baselines", "Mark the approved change request as fully implemented in the Change Log", "Include the approved change request in the Change Log"]', 1, 'The question states that the request for additional scope has been approved, making it an approved change request. Once a change request is approved, the project management plan and/or the project documents may be revised. Making these revisions is the responsibility of the project manager. Unless the project manager has the authority to approve change requests, the approved change requests are the primary mechanism for communicating changes to the project documents. The approved change requests become part of the project documents and the project management plan is then updated. In this scenario, the Change Log is the project document that should be updated to reflect the approved change request associated with the increase in scope. The approved change request has been submitted to the Change Log and the project manager is responsible for updating the project management plan and any other project documents as needed. Of the choices provided, only marking the Change Log as fully implemented is a responsibility of the project manager and is the best course of action in this scenario.', 'Gestão das Aquisições', '2025-05-17 00:13:49', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', 12, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (26, 'You are working on a project to upgrade the company''s computer systems. You need to purchase hundreds of new desktop computers, monitors, and printers.  What is the best way to obtain the hardware?', '["Iniciar uma competi\u00e7\u00e3o aberta com os vendedores", "Solicitar or\u00e7amentos de diferentes fornecedores", "Fazer um pedido direto ao fornecedor preferido", "Comprar o hardware diretamente de uma loja de varejo"]', 1, 'Para adquirir os equipamentos necessários para o projeto, a equipe de gerenciamento de projetos deve considerar as aquisições como descritas no processo Planejar Compras e Aquisições. Durante este processo, a equipe de gerenciamento de projetos se concentra em determinar o que comprar ou adquirir e identificar potenciais vendedores. Em um projeto, a equipe do projeto pode alocar responsabilidade e autoridade para a realização de atividades específicas para um fornecedor por meio de um contrato. Uma das ferramentas e técnicas usadas para coletar informações sobre os fornecedores é a solicitação de informações, cotação ou proposta, ou seja, a solicitação de orçamentos de diferentes fornecedores. A partir da informação recebida dos fornecedores, a equipe do projeto pode avaliar as possibilidades e selecionar o fornecedor mais adequado para as necessidades do projeto', 'Gestão das Aquisições', '2025-05-17 00:13:49', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', 12, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (27, 'Qual é a ação correta a ser tomada quando requisitos são identificados como fora do escopo do projeto?', '["C. Analisar e avaliar o impacto antes de inclu\u00ed-los no escopo", "B. Rejeit\u00e1-los e manter o escopo original", "D. Delegar a decis\u00e3o para o cliente", "A. Inclu\u00ed-los no escopo do projeto sem an\u00e1lise adicional"]', 0, 'Ao identificar requisitos fora do escopo do projeto, a melhor prática é registrá-los como requisitos fora do escopo e comunicar essa decisão aos stakeholders. Isso ajuda a manter o foco no escopo definido e a evitar possíveis alterações não controladas que poderiam impactar o projeto.', 'Gestão do Escopo', '2025-05-17 00:25:05', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', 7, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (28, 'O que representa a situação em que o escopo do projeto começa a se expandir devido à inclusão de novas demandas não previstas inicialmente?', '["A. Aceitar a solicita\u00e7\u00e3o sem avaliar o impacto", "C. Avaliar o impacto da solicita\u00e7\u00e3o por meio de an\u00e1lise de mudan\u00e7a de controle", "D. Implementar a solicita\u00e7\u00e3o sem informar a equipe", "B. Negar imediatamente a solicita\u00e7\u00e3o para manter o projeto no curso"]', 1, 'O termo ''Escopo adicional'' é utilizado para descrever novas demandas que surgem ao longo do projeto e que não estavam inicialmente previstas no escopo definido. Essas demandas podem resultar em trabalhos extras a serem realizados.', 'Gestão do Escopo', '2025-05-17 00:25:09', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', 7, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (29, 'Qual é a principal finalidade da declaração de escopo do projeto?', '["B. Ignorar as expectativas conflitantes e seguir o plano inicial", "C. Realizar uma an\u00e1lise de requisitos para equilibrar as expectativas", "A. Atender apenas \u00e0s expectativas das partes interessadas mais influentes", "D. Alterar o escopo sem consultar as partes interessadas"]', 1, 'A declaração de escopo do projeto tem como principal finalidade documentar de forma clara e concisa o que está incluído e o que está excluído do projeto, ou seja, os requisitos do projeto. Isso ajuda a garantir que todas as partes interessadas tenham uma compreensão comum do que será entregue no projeto.', 'Gestão do Escopo', '2025-05-17 00:25:13', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', 5, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (30, 'Qual termo se refere ao trabalho adicional não planejado que pode impactar o escopo do projeto?', '["C. Avaliar o impacto da atividade e ajustar o escopo conforme necess\u00e1rio", "D. Delegar a decis\u00e3o para a equipe de execu\u00e7\u00e3o", "A. Incluir a atividade sem avaliar o impacto no escopo", "B. Remover a atividade para manter o escopo original"]', 0, 'Mudanças no Escopo referem-se a alterações no que foi originalmente planejado para o projeto. Quando novas demandas surgem, elas podem impactar o escopo do projeto e exigir ajustes no plano para acomodá-las.', 'Gestão do Escopo', '2025-05-17 00:25:17', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', 7, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (31, 'Qual das seguintes atividades NÃO faz parte do processo de definição do escopo?', '["C. Avaliar o impacto e, se vi\u00e1vel, incluir o requisito mediante aprova\u00e7\u00e3o formal", "D. Atrasar a decis\u00e3o para a pr\u00f3xima fase do projeto", "A. Incluir o novo requisito para agradar o stakeholder", "B. Recusar a solicita\u00e7\u00e3o devido ao est\u00e1gio avan\u00e7ado do projeto"]', 0, 'Durante a definição do escopo do projeto, a análise de riscos geralmente é realizada em um processo separado chamado Gerenciamento de Riscos do Projeto, que está relacionado ao escopo, mas não faz parte da definição do escopo em si. A análise de riscos ajuda a identificar e gerenciar potenciais ameaças e oportunidades que podem afetar o projeto.', 'Gestão do Escopo', '2025-05-17 00:25:20', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', 5, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (32, 'Qual das seguintes atividades NÃO faz parte do processo de definição do escopo do projeto?', '["C) Ignorar o novo requisito e seguir o plano inicial", "D) Designar um novo gerente de projeto para lidar com o novo requisito", "B) Avaliar o impacto do novo requisito no escopo e no prazo do projeto antes de inclu\u00ed-lo", "A) Incluir imediatamente o novo requisito no escopo do projeto"]', 2, 'Desenvolver o cronograma do projeto faz parte do gerenciamento do tempo do projeto, não do escopo. Durante a definição do escopo, atividades como coletar requisitos, criar a EAP e validar o escopo são fundamentais para garantir que o escopo do projeto seja claramente definido e compreendido por todas as partes envolvidas.', 'Gestão do Escopo', '2025-05-17 08:31:38', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', 5, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (33, 'Qual a principal finalidade de definir o escopo do projeto durante a fase de iniciação?', '["D) Implementar a mudan\u00e7a sem avalia\u00e7\u00e3o, assumindo os riscos envolvidos", "B) Avaliar o impacto da mudan\u00e7a no escopo, prazo e custo do projeto antes de tomar uma decis\u00e3o", "C) Negar a solicita\u00e7\u00e3o do cliente para manter o escopo original", "A) Aceitar a mudan\u00e7a imediatamente para satisfazer o cliente"]', 1, 'Durante a definição do escopo do projeto, é essencial determinar claramente o que está incluído no projeto (escopo do produto) e o que está excluído (escopo excluído). Isso ajuda a evitar escopo inchado ou indefinido, garantindo que todos os envolvidos tenham uma compreensão clara do que será entregue.', 'Gestão do Escopo', '2025-05-17 08:31:41', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', 5, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (34, 'Qual é a melhor abordagem para lidar com essa solicitação de mudança de escopo?', '["C) Delegar a responsabilidade da nova atividade para um membro da equipe sem an\u00e1lise pr\u00e9via", "A) Incluir imediatamente a nova atividade no escopo do projeto", "B) Avaliar a necessidade e impacto da nova atividade no escopo e no prazo do projeto antes de tom\u00e1-la", "D) Ignorar a nova atividade e continuar com o plano original"]', 2, 'A melhor abordagem é realizar uma análise de impacto da inclusão da piscina no escopo do projeto para avaliar como essa mudança afetará prazos, custos, recursos e demais entregas. Além disso, é fundamental obter a aprovação formal do cliente para garantir que as expectativas estejam alinhadas e que a mudança seja controlada de acordo com os processos de gerenciamento de mudanças.', 'Gestão do Escopo', '2025-05-17 08:31:45', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', 7, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (35, 'Qual é a principal razão para documentar claramente os requisitos do projeto durante a fase de iniciação?', '["A) Alterar o escopo planejado para se adequar ao escopo real executado", "B) Identificar as causas das diverg\u00eancias e implementar a\u00e7\u00f5es corretivas para alinhar o escopo \u00e0 situa\u00e7\u00e3o planejada", "C) Ignorar as diferen\u00e7as e continuar com o escopo real executado", "D) Solicitar ao cliente que ajuste suas expectativas em rela\u00e7\u00e3o ao escopo"]', 1, 'Documentar claramente os requisitos do projeto durante a fase de iniciação é fundamental para estabelecer uma base sólida e comum de entendimento entre todos os envolvidos no projeto. Isso ajuda a evitar mal-entendidos, conflitos e retrabalho futuro, garantindo que todos estejam alinhados em relação ao que é esperado do projeto.', 'Gestão do Escopo', '2025-05-17 08:31:49', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', 5, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (36, 'Qual é o principal objetivo ao definir o escopo de um projeto?', '["C) Ocultar as falhas das entregas para evitar problemas durante o encerramento do projeto", "D) Transferir a responsabilidade pelas falhas para a equipe de execu\u00e7\u00e3o sem investiga\u00e7\u00e3o", "A) Considerar as entregas incompletas como aceit\u00e1veis e encerrar o projeto", "B) Realizar uma an\u00e1lise dos impactos das entregas incompletas e tomar medidas para corrigir as falhas"]', 3, 'O principal objetivo ao definir o escopo de um projeto é garantir que todas as atividades necessárias para atender aos requisitos do projeto sejam incluídas. Isso ajuda a evitar lacunas na entrega e a assegurar que o projeto alcance seus objetivos.', 'Gestão do Escopo', '2025-05-17 08:31:52', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', 7, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (37, 'Como a equipe de gerenciamento de projetos pode lidar com o impacto dos custos de produção dos materiais de construção decorrente da nova legislação durante a execução do projeto?', '["Uma abordagem eficaz para lidar com o aumento significativo nos custos dos materiais de constru\u00e7\u00e3o devido a varia\u00e7\u00f5es cambiais durante a execu\u00e7\u00e3o do projeto seria a revis\u00e3o e atualiza\u00e7\u00e3o do Plano de Gerenciamento de Custos do projeto, buscando identificar as \u00e1reas impactadas e desenvolver estrat\u00e9gias para mitigar o aumento dos custos, como renegocia\u00e7\u00e3o de contratos, busca por novos fornecedores ou realoca\u00e7\u00e3o de recursos.", "Diante do aumento nos custos, uma a\u00e7\u00e3o eficaz seria cortar drasticamente o escopo do projeto para compensar os gastos extras com materiais de constru\u00e7\u00e3o, mantendo o or\u00e7amento inicial.", "Para gerenciar o aumento nos custos dos materiais, uma estrat\u00e9gia eficaz seria transferir a responsabilidade para a equipe de compras, sem acompanhamento ou revis\u00e3o do impacto nos custos totais do projeto.", "Uma abordagem eficaz para lidar com o aumento nos custos seria ignorar o impacto financeiro e continuar a execu\u00e7\u00e3o do projeto normalmente, confiando que a situa\u00e7\u00e3o se resolver\u00e1 sozinha."]', 0, 'Ao adotar a estratégia de controle de riscos, a equipe de gerenciamento de projetos poderá identificar medidas para reduzir o impacto financeiro dos custos de produção dos materiais de construção devido à nova legislação. Esta abordagem está alinhada com as boas práticas do PMBOK, que recomenda a análise e planejamento de respostas aos riscos identificados durante a execução do projeto para minimizar impactos negativos e maximizar oportunidades.', 'Gestão do Custo', '2025-05-17 08:42:07', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', 6, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (38, 'Considerando a necessidade de contratar um consultor externo para monitorar os preços dos materiais de construção, como a equipe de gerenciamento de projetos pode garantir que esse custo adicional seja adequadamente controlado e documentado dentro do orçamento do projeto?', '["Outra estrat\u00e9gia vi\u00e1vel seria buscar patrocinadores adicionais para financiar as a\u00e7\u00f5es de mitiga\u00e7\u00e3o de riscos, assegurando que o projeto permane\u00e7a dentro das restri\u00e7\u00f5es or\u00e7ament\u00e1rias estabelecidas.", "Uma op\u00e7\u00e3o a considerar seria renegociar os prazos de entrega do projeto com os stakeholders, de forma a acomodar os custos extras gerados pelas a\u00e7\u00f5es de mitiga\u00e7\u00e3o de riscos e manter o or\u00e7amento planejado.", "A equipe de gerenciamento de projetos pode lidar com o aumento nos custos causado por a\u00e7\u00f5es de mitiga\u00e7\u00e3o de riscos atrav\u00e9s da reserva de conting\u00eancia. Esta reserva adicional de recursos financeiros \u00e9 inclu\u00edda no or\u00e7amento do projeto para cobrir custos imprevistos relacionados \u00e0 gest\u00e3o de riscos. Dessa forma, ao implementar a\u00e7\u00f5es de mitiga\u00e7\u00e3o, os custos adicionais podem ser absorvidos pela reserva de conting\u00eancia, mantendo o projeto dentro do or\u00e7amento planejado.", "Uma abordagem alternativa seria aumentar o escopo do projeto para absorver os custos adicionais de mitiga\u00e7\u00e3o de riscos, garantindo que o or\u00e7amento original n\u00e3o seja comprometido."]', 2, 'Ao incluir o custo do consultor externo no plano de gerenciamento de custos, a equipe garante que esse valor esteja previsto e aprovado dentro do orçamento do projeto. Estabelecer critérios claros para autorização de despesas adicionais ajuda a evitar gastos não planejados. Monitorar regularmente os gastos relacionados ao consultor permite identificar desvios e tomar ações corretivas. Registrar todas as informações financeiras de forma transparente e precisa contribui para a visibilidade e controle dos custos do projeto.', 'Gestão do Custo', '2025-05-17 08:42:13', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', 6, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (39, 'Como o gerente de projeto pode controlar e gerenciar os custos adicionais decorrentes da estratégia de mitigação adotada para o risco de entrega atrasada de materiais de construção?', '["Uma alternativa vi\u00e1vel seria renegociar os contratos de fornecimento para incluir cl\u00e1usulas de reajuste de pre\u00e7o conforme a varia\u00e7\u00e3o do mercado, garantindo maior previsibilidade nos custos.", "A equipe de projeto poderia ter melhor gerenciado o custo dos materiais de constru\u00e7\u00e3o diante da varia\u00e7\u00e3o de pre\u00e7os inesperada atrav\u00e9s da estrat\u00e9gia de reduzir ou controlar o risco, implementando um plano de conting\u00eancia que inclu\u00edsse a compra antecipada de materiais ou a negocia\u00e7\u00e3o de contratos de fornecimento com cl\u00e1usulas de ajuste de pre\u00e7o.", "A equipe poderia ter realizado um levantamento de pre\u00e7os de materiais em diferentes fornecedores para garantir o melhor custo-benef\u00edcio diante da varia\u00e7\u00e3o de pre\u00e7os inesperada.", "Outra abordagem eficaz seria diversificar os fornecedores de materiais para reduzir a depend\u00eancia de um \u00fanico fornecedor e minimizar os impactos das varia\u00e7\u00f5es de pre\u00e7os."]', 1, 'Ao utilizar reservas de contingência, o gerente de projeto pode alocar recursos financeiros adicionais para lidar especificamente com os custos extras resultantes da estratégia de mitigação adotada. Essas reservas são planejadas antecipadamente durante o planejamento do projeto, com base na análise de riscos e incertezas, e são utilizadas para cobrir custos imprevistos e não previstos no orçamento inicial. Dessa forma, a equipe do projeto pode implementar a estratégia de mitigação sem comprometer o orçamento principal estabelecido.', 'Gestão do Custo', '2025-05-17 08:42:19', '7-Iniciando um projeto_ Análise de Stakeholder, RACI, fail causes, resources, project charter, tools.pdf', 12, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (40, 'Como a equipe de gerenciamento de projetos poderia ter melhor previsto e gerenciado os impactos financeiros decorrentes do aumento dos preços dos materiais de construção?', '["A equipe de gerenciamento de projetos poderia ter evitado ou reduzido o estouro na reserva de conting\u00eancia devido ao aumento nos pre\u00e7os dos materiais de constru\u00e7\u00e3o realizando uma an\u00e1lise de riscos mais detalhada no in\u00edcio do projeto, identificando a possibilidade do aumento de pre\u00e7os como um risco significativo. Com essa identifica\u00e7\u00e3o, poderiam ter desenvolvido planos de conting\u00eancia espec\u00edficos, como estabelecer contratos de fornecimento a longo prazo com os fornecedores atuais, buscar fornecedores alternativos com pre\u00e7os mais est\u00e1veis ou incluir cl\u00e1usulas de reajuste de pre\u00e7os nos contratos existentes.", "Uma estrat\u00e9gia eficaz para reduzir o estouro na reserva de conting\u00eancia seria implementar um sistema de alerta precoce para mudan\u00e7as nos pre\u00e7os dos materiais, permitindo a\u00e7\u00f5es preventivas imediatas.", "A equipe de gerenciamento poderia ter evitado o estouro da reserva contingencial ao monitorar ativamente os pre\u00e7os dos materiais e renegociar contratos antecipadamente, buscando cl\u00e1usulas de reajuste autom\u00e1ticas.", "Para evitar o estouro na reserva de conting\u00eancia, a equipe poderia ter investido em treinamento para os membros sobre an\u00e1lise de custos e atualiza\u00e7\u00f5es de mercado, aprimorando a capacidade de prever varia\u00e7\u00f5es de pre\u00e7os."]', 0, 'Ao incluir reservas de contingência no orçamento do projeto, a equipe de gerenciamento estaria se preparando para possíveis aumentos nos preços dos materiais de construção, mitigando assim o impacto financeiro dessas variações. Isso está alinhado com as boas práticas de gerenciamento de custos, conforme descritas no PMBOK, que recomendam a inclusão de reservas para lidar com incertezas e riscos que possam afetar o orçamento do projeto.', 'Gestão do Custo', '2025-05-17 08:42:26', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', 6, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (41, 'Considerando o cenário apresentado, como a equipe de gerenciamento de projetos poderia ter se preparado melhor para lidar com a variação no custo dos materiais e minimizar o impacto financeiro no projeto?', '["Em vez de elaborar reservas de conting\u00eancia adequadas para poss\u00edveis varia\u00e7\u00f5es de custo, a equipe de gerenciamento poderia ter optado por cortar custos iniciais, comprometendo a qualidade do projeto.", "A equipe de gerenciamento de projetos poderia ter se preparado melhor para lidar com varia\u00e7\u00f5es de custo inesperadas durante a execu\u00e7\u00e3o do projeto, estabelecendo um or\u00e7amento fixo e r\u00edgido desde o in\u00edcio, sem considerar poss\u00edveis imprevistos.", "A equipe de gerenciamento de projetos poderia ter se preparado melhor para lidar com varia\u00e7\u00f5es de custo inesperadas durante a execu\u00e7\u00e3o do projeto atrav\u00e9s de uma an\u00e1lise detalhada do or\u00e7amento, identifica\u00e7\u00e3o de potenciais fontes de varia\u00e7\u00e3o de custo, elabora\u00e7\u00e3o de reservas de conting\u00eancia adequadas e monitoramento constante do desempenho financeiro do projeto.", "Uma abordagem mais eficaz para lidar com varia\u00e7\u00f5es de custo inesperadas durante a execu\u00e7\u00e3o do projeto teria sido ignorar completamente a an\u00e1lise detalhada do or\u00e7amento e confiar apenas na intui\u00e7\u00e3o dos membros da equipe."]', 2, 'Identificar o risco de variação no custo dos materiais antecipadamente permite que a equipe de gerenciamento de projetos desenvolva estratégias de mitigação adequadas, como a alocação de reservas de contingência específicas para lidar com esses custos inesperados. A comunicação transparente aos stakeholders sobre esse risco possibilita a obtenção de apoio e entendimento em caso de necessidade de utilização das reservas de contingência, garantindo a transparência e a confiança no processo de gerenciamento de custos do projeto.', 'Gestão do Custo', '2025-05-17 08:42:34', '5-Iniciando um projeto_ Key Components, Custo_benefício e Project Charter.pdf', 6, '{}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (42, 'A project is in the planning phase, and the team has just finished creating the project management plan.  What is the first thing the project manager should do with this document?', '["Review the document with the project management team", "Use it as a guide for the project work", "Give the project management plan to the project sponsor", "Distribute the project management plan to the stakeholders"]', 'Distribute the project management plan to the stakeholders', 'The question states that the project is in the planning phase and the project manager has just finished creating the project management plan. The scope of the project management plan can vary based on the needs of the project. In general, the project management plan and its subsidiary plans are created and refined as the project progresses. In the initial stages of the project, the project management plan may be a single document. As the project progresses and the project management plan is elaborated, it will likely contain many subsidiary plans and other components. The project management plan is the primary output from the process 4.2 Develop Project Management Plan. The development of the project management plan is an iterative process and the project management team may use tools and techniques from other planning processes in an effort to create the project management plan. Once the project management plan has been developed, the project manager and project management team need to ensure that the project management plan is available to the project team and key stakeholders. By distributing the project management plan, the project manager will ensure that the team and key stakeholders are working from the same set of expectations and guidelines.', 'Gestão da Integração', '2025-05-17 09:24:33', NULL, NULL, '{"summary_id": 4, "generated_at": "2025-05-17T06:24:33.305050"}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (43, 'You are managing a large software development project with many teams who are developing multiple features for the application.  How can you best align all of the team''s work to meet the project objectives?', '["Facilitating regular meetings between the project team members to discuss the status of each feature", "Using the Perform Integrated Change Control process to approve all changes to the project work", "Leveraging the Monitor and Control Project Work process to track the progress of the individual features", "Communicating and periodically revisiting the project charter to ensure that all work aligns with the project objectives"]', 'Communicating and periodically revisiting the project charter to ensure that all work aligns with the project objectives', 'In the scenario described, a project manager is managing a large software development project with numerous teams working on multiple features. It''s not uncommon for project teams to get caught up in the details of their work and lose sight of the bigger picture. The project charter, as one of the key outputs of the Develop Project Charter process, is a document that formally authorizes the project and provides the project manager with the authority to apply organizational resources to project activities. The project charter also provides the project manager with the authority to communicate the purpose of the project and the expected business value to the project participants. The project charter is a key project management deliverable that, when communicated to all project participants and periodically revisited, can help ensure that all project work is aligned with the project objectives. While the Perform Integrated Change Control and Monitor and Control Project Work processes may also help align the team''s work with the project objectives, these processes are not directly connected to the ensuring the project objectives are aligned with all of the project work.', 'Gestão da Integração', '2025-05-17 09:24:33', NULL, NULL, '{"summary_id": 4, "generated_at": "2025-05-17T06:24:33.321678"}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (44, 'You are managing a project to design and build a new kind of electric car. You have just released the project management plan and other project documents to your team.  What should you do next?', '["Prepare the project charter", "Identify the stakeholders", "Start the project work activities", "Create the project charter"]', 'Create the project charter', 'The scenario does not specifically state that the project charter has been developed or approved. The project charter is the document issued by the project initiator or sponsor that formally authorizes the existence of a project and provides the project manager with the authority to apply organizational resources to project activities. Although the project charter may be considered a project initiation document (as mentioned in the question), the project charter is a component of the overall project management plan. The project charter formally authorizes the project. The project charter recognizes the existence of the project. The project charter provides the project manager with the authority to apply organizational resources to project activities. The project charter contains much of the information that the project manager will use throughout the project to manage the project. The project charter is a key output of the Develop Project Charter process. Therefore, of the choices provided, the next best action is to prepare the project charter', 'Gestão da Integração', '2025-05-17 09:24:33', NULL, NULL, '{"summary_id": 4, "generated_at": "2025-05-17T06:24:33.321678"}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (45, 'Your project is in trouble due to too many changes to the requirements. The gold plating and the frequent uncontrolled changes have caused the project to be behind schedule, over budget, and the deliverables not entirely fit for the intended use.  What could have prevented the situation?', '["Implementing a strict scope management plan", "Including more details in the project management plan", "Completing the project earlier to minimize the risks", "Developing a comprehensive change management plan"]', 'Developing a comprehensive change management plan', 'Gold plating and excessive uncontrolled changes to the project requirements are examples of scope creep. A comprehensive change management plan is one of the tools and techniques of the Plan Scope Management process. The plan typically includes the steps for requesting a change, along with the process of reviewing, approving, and declining the change request. The change management plan can also specify the change control board''s composition and working procedure. A well-structured change management plan can prevent scope creep and help the project manager to manage the changes and their impact on the project''s performance.', 'Gestão da Integração', '2025-05-17 09:24:33', NULL, NULL, '{"summary_id": 4, "generated_at": "2025-05-17T06:24:33.338359"}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (46, 'You are the project manager for a software development project. The project involves working with a new programming language, and as a result, you expect there to be more than the usual amount of rework.  What should you do to handle this situation?', '["Add more time to the schedule to account for the rework", "Create a change request to adjust the project management plan", "Reduce the project schedule to minimize the rework necessary", "Revisit the project management plan and make changes as necessary"]', 'Revisit the project management plan and make changes as necessary', 'Although many of the possible answers might be correct, revisiting the project management plan and making changes as necessary is the best answer. The project manager is expecting more rework than normal because the project is using a new programming language. The project management plan includes the schedule management plan, which contains the schedule baseline and the schedule management approach. The schedule baseline is the approved version of a schedule model that can be changed only through formal change control procedures. The schedule management approach provides guidance to project scheduling. The project manager will most likely have to adjust the schedule to account for the additional rework. The changes to the schedule may require adjustments to the project management plan. The project management plan is a subsidiary of the project management plan and is used to manage the execution of a project. Thus, revisiting the project management plan and making changes as necessary is the best course of action', 'Gestão da Integração', '2025-05-17 09:24:33', NULL, NULL, '{"summary_id": 4, "generated_at": "2025-05-17T06:24:33.338359"}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (47, 'A project is in the execution phase. A team member informs you that some of the defined requirements are not needed. If implemented, they could potentially lead to rework and wasted resources.  What is the best course of action for you to take?', '["Bound the project to the current project scope, schedule, and cost baseline", "Delegate the decision to the team member since they have the best understanding of the situation", "Submit a change request to the change control board (CCB) to determine the best course of action", "Evaluate the impact of not including the requirements and approve the change if appropriate"]', 'Evaluate the impact of not including the requirements and approve the change if appropriate', 'The scenario implies that the team member is suggesting a change request for the project to exclude some of the project requirements. A change request is a document that formally requests a change to the project, with the change control board (CCB) being the group of stakeholders that is normally responsible for approving changes. Although the change request could be submitted by any stakeholder, it is typically the responsibility of the project manager to ensure that any such requests are properly documented and submitted to the CCB for review and decision. Among the answer choices provided, only one represents a direct response to the scenario. That is, the project manager should evaluate the impact of not including the requirements and approve the change if appropriate. Bounding the project is a technique used during the Develop Project Management Plan process to obtain stakeholder and sponsor approval of the project scope, cost, schedule and other project management plans. It is too late in the project for the project manager to be performing this exercise. The scenario does not suggest that the project manager is delegating the decision to the team member. The project manager is responsible for ensuring that the decision-making process is followed and that the appropriate stakeholders are involved in the decision. The question implies that the project manager is following the Perform Integrated Change Control process. Therefore, the approved change to the project requirements should be documented in the project management plan and communicated to the appropriate stakeholders.', 'Gestão da Integração', '2025-05-17 09:24:33', NULL, NULL, '{"summary_id": 4, "generated_at": "2025-05-17T06:24:33.355037"}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (48, 'A project manager is leading a project to develop a new software application. A change request has been approved to adjust the schedule and the cost baseline.  What should the project manager do next?', '["Update the project schedule and the project management plan", "Inform the project sponsor of the approved change request", "Delay the implementation of the approved change request", "Update the project documents"]', 'Update the project documents', 'Approved change requests can require an update to the project documents. If the schedule and cost baselines are changed, then the project documents need to be updated to reflect those changes.', 'Gestão da Integração', '2025-05-17 09:24:33', NULL, NULL, '{"summary_id": 4, "generated_at": "2025-05-17T06:24:33.355037"}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (49, 'You are a project manager for a software development project. The project team is currently planning the next sprint.  What should you do first?', '["Review the product backlog with the project team", "Update the risk register for the agile project", "Inspect the performance data of the agile team", "Conduct the daily stand-up meeting"]', 'Conduct the daily stand-up meeting', 'The project manager in this scenario is using an adaptive or agile approach to managing the project. Conducting the daily stand-up meeting is an agile best practice and should be done first to kick off the sprint. The daily stand-up meeting, also known as the daily scrum, is a daily meeting to inspect progress toward the sprint goal. The purpose of the daily stand-up meeting is to determine what work has been completed, what work will be done next, and what obstacles are in the way of the team achieving the sprint goal. The daily stand-up meeting provides a regular opportunity for the team to assess its progress and adjust as needed. The daily stand-up meeting is a best practice in the agile methodology and is an example of the benefits of an agile approach as described in the scenario', 'Gestão da Integração', '2025-05-17 09:24:33', NULL, NULL, '{"summary_id": 4, "generated_at": "2025-05-17T06:24:33.371720"}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (50, 'You are managing a large project to build a new plant. Your project is currently in the execution phase, and you just received a change request to replace the safety gates with a more efficient and less expensive model.  What is your first course of action?', '["Examine the potential benefits of implementing the requested change", "Consult the change log to review how similar change requests were handled", "Call a meeting of the change control board to discuss the requested change", "Consider the potential risks of changing the safety gates"]', 'Consider the potential risks of changing the safety gates', 'The scenario describes an identified change request that requires evaluation. Approved change requests are typically the primary input to the Direct and Manage Project Work process. However, before an approved change request can be implemented, the project manager must assess the potential impact of the change on the project. The potential impacts of changing the safety gates are discussed in the corresponding change control board meeting. The project manager and the team consider the potential risks of the change and decide if the change is worth the expected benefits. This decision is documented in the change log. The change log is one of the outputs of the Direct and Manage Project Work process and a key tool in the Manage Project Knowledge process', 'Gestão da Integração', '2025-05-17 09:24:33', NULL, NULL, '{"summary_id": 4, "generated_at": "2025-05-17T06:24:33.371720"}');
INSERT INTO questions VALUES (51, 'During project executing, a team member informs you that she is not able to complete one of the project activities within the planned schedule.  What should you do first?', '["Consult the project team to determine what should be done with this team member", "Meet with the project sponsor to determine how to proceed with the project", "Ask the project management office (PMO) for advice on how to handle this situation", "Review the project documents to determine the impact of the activity on the project''s schedule"]', 'Review the project documents to determine the impact of the activity on the project''s schedule', 'Although there are several potential courses of action available to you as a project manager in this situation, the best course of action is to review the project documents to determine the impact of the activity on the project''s schedule. This is a situation in which the project manager may have to make some concessions and allow the team to complete the activity as quickly as possible while still maintaining the quality of the deliverable. The project schedule should be considered as a dynamic plan that may require modification as the project progresses. Therefore, it is critical to understand the project''s schedule and the implications of making changes to it before deciding on the best course of action. The set of project documents that should be reviewed includes the project schedule, risk register, issue log, and project scope statement. The project scope statement and the WBS can help you understand the relationship between the activity in question and the project''s scope. The risk register may help you determine if this situation was identified as a risk during the project''s planning. The issue log may describe similar issues in the past and suggest potential solutions. The project schedule should help you understand the implications of moving this milestone for the other project activities and the project''s critical path', 'Gestão da Integração', '2025-05-17 09:24:33', NULL, NULL, '{"summary_id": 4, "generated_at": "2025-05-17T06:24:33.388298"}');


